title: Do It Yourself - Fall 2013 (gnv64)
description:
Do It Yourself - Fall 2013
English | PDF | 116 pages | 19.8 mb

FEATURES
46 WOOD WORK
Tour the happily renovated home of a photographer and crafter and their two young children.
54 ABOVE THE FOLD
Follow our step-by-step photos to told your way to gorgeous origami-inspired projects. This ancient technique never looked so fresh.
64 ROCK THE BLOCK 
Employ everything from hairpins to a kitchen whisk to create hip blockprinted home decor for your dining room, bedroom. and more.
72 BRANCH OUT
Take a cue from the great outdoors, Learn how to build a desk that highlights natural wood tones and two beautiful birch logs, plus a branch-theme shelt display.
78 FRESH PERSPECTIVE
Learn how to incorporate Pinterest-worthy trends-gold-Ieating. geometric patterns, and furniture hacks-into your living spaces.
84 ROLL WITH IT
Today's wallpapers are tresh. tun. and easier than ever to apply. See six fresh projects-some using just a scrapand learn how to wallpaper.
92 MAKING IT WORK
This Midwest couple combine the things they love (his motorcycle) and love to make (her art) into a one-of-a-kind abode.
102 BRILLIANT BURLAP
At just a few dollars per yard, this material has a humble reputation but packs a style punch when used for pillows, wall art, and other easy-do home decor.

10 TRY IT 
Tackle a new technique! Resilient resin is a perfect material for tiny treasures. such as buttons, photo frames, and napkin rings.
18 ORDER IN THE HOUSE
Whip outdoor clutter into shape before winter.
22 WHAT TO DO WITH ... 
Before you recycle your used books. check out this wall collage crafted from old tomes.
27 ON OUR RADAR 
These smart products will make life easier-and prettier! From new books to must-have kits, this roundup features our faves in DIY decorating!
32 COOL TOOLS
Are your saw skills sharp? Learn the best tool for your project with our handy guide.
35 FAST KITCHEN FACELIFTS
Quick cabinet makeovers and simple knob replacements make a huge impact on a tiny budget.
112 BEST OF ETSY
Foxes, squirrels, and bunnies. oh my! OUr fall finds from etsy.com bring out the wild side
